That's my seat, number 30.

35
00:04:57,490 --> 00:04:58,110
What?

36
00:04:58,900 --> 00:05:00,700
I'm 30.

37
00:05:04,330 --> 00:05:07,160
Oh, I'm next to you. Sorry.

38
00:05:07,160 --> 00:05:08,500
No, no, no, no, no.

39
00:05:08,500 --> 00:05:10,500
You sit here. It's fine.

40
00:05:13,000 --> 00:05:14,380
Hello, I'm 31.

41
00:05:14,380 --> 00:05:15,710
Oh, sorry, sorry.

42
00:05:24,760 --> 00:05:29,270
We're departing. Please fasten your seat belts.

43
00:06:29,580 --> 00:06:33,120
-Oh, it scared me.
-What happened?

44
00:06:38,880 --> 00:06:43,090
Seoul, Goseong
Domee Express

45
00:06:45,760 --> 00:06:47,550
Oh, that was close.

46
00:06:48,470 --> 00:06:49,560
Are you okay?

47
00:06:50,560 --> 00:06:52,730
-Was there an accident?
-What's wrong?

48
00:06:53,230 --> 00:06:54,190
It's okay.

49
00:06:57,150 --> 00:06:57,860
This is yours.

50
00:06:57,860 --> 00:06:58,820
Oh, thank you.

51
00:06:59,940 --> 00:07:01,030
Is this me?

52
00:07:01,480 --> 00:07:03,320
No, no, it's not.

53
00:07:03,740 --> 00:07:04,650
It is me.

54
00:07:10,450 --> 00:07:11,330
Sorry.

55
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:14,910
It's okay. I'm quite happy.

56
00:07:16,420 --> 00:07:20,130
There's a mudslide ahead; we can't go on.

57
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:23,630
It'll take several hours to restore.

58
00:07:24,050 --> 00:07:25,840
Everyone should call someone to pick you up if you can.

59
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:28,340
What if we can't?

60
00:07:28,340 --> 00:07:31,100
Then we just wait. What else can we do?

61
00:07:31,510 --> 00:07:33,020
-What to do?
-Who can we call?

62
00:07:33,020 --> 00:07:35,310
Attention passengers.

63
00:07:35,310 --> 00:07:40,190
Due to weather conditions, takeoff can't happen.

64
00:07:40,190 --> 00:07:41,150
Has it been canceled?

65
00:07:41,150 --> 00:07:41,980
Please disembark in order and wait in the lounge.

66
00:07:41,980 --> 00:07:43,820
We will assist you with rescheduling.

67
00:07:43,820 --> 00:07:44,740
Please disembark in order.

68
00:07:44,740 --> 00:07:46,820
Reschedule after disembarking.

69
00:08:05,840 --> 00:08:06,840
Excuse me.

70
00:08:08,800 --> 00:08:10,510
Could you move aside?

71
00:08:10,970 --> 00:08:12,100
Oh, sure.

72
00:08:16,520 --> 00:08:17,730
I'm finished.

73
00:08:18,440 --> 00:08:19,310
Oh, okay.

74
00:08:29,110 --> 00:08:31,160
Give me that drawing from earlier.

75
00:08:32,780 --> 00:08:34,200
That drawing?

76
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:36,700
Don't worry. I already threw it away.

77
00:08:37,370 --> 00:08:38,750
I want it.

78
00:08:39,870 --> 00:08:40,750
Got it.

79
00:08:43,170 --> 00:08:44,210
Wait.

80
00:08:54,350 --> 00:08:55,310
Here.

81
00:09:10,320 --> 00:09:11,280
Thank you.

82
00:09:11,490 --> 00:09:12,280
You're welcome.

83
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:21,080
Hello?

84
00:09:24,460 --> 00:09:26,340
Dad, the mountain collapsed.

85
00:09:26,340 --> 00:09:28,380
I knew it would collapse sooner or later.

86
00:09:28,970 --> 00:09:29,840
Get in the car.

87
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:31,130
What the hell is this?

88
00:09:43,100 --> 00:09:43,900
Wait.

89
00:09:49,610 --> 00:09:50,490
Well...

90
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:54,160
What's wrong?

91
00:09:55,320 --> 00:09:56,280
Well...

92
00:09:57,330 --> 00:09:58,740
Please calm down.

93
00:09:59,330 --> 00:10:01,790
Everyone, please calm down. We are so sorry.

94
00:10:02,160 --> 00:10:03,120
Please get in the line.

95
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:04,580
There's no room available.

96
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:06,290
You should try the next hotel.

97
00:10:06,290 --> 00:10:07,460
Is there any room left?

98
00:10:08,130 --> 00:10:09,130
We're sorry.

99
00:10:09,510 --> 00:10:12,380
This gentleman took the last room.

100
00:10:26,980 --> 00:10:27,820
Come in.

101
00:10:28,650 --> 00:10:29,530
Yeah.

102
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:11,280
Kathleen has passed this area.

103
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:14,360
But the situation in Korea doesn't look good.

104
00:11:15,490 --> 00:11:16,490
What did it say?

105
00:11:16,490 --> 00:11:19,030
It's said to be the strongest typhoon in eighty years.

106
00:11:20,080 --> 00:11:21,740
The night market must be destroyed.

107
00:11:22,540 --> 00:11:23,450
The night market?

108
00:11:24,540 --> 00:11:25,460
Yeah, here.

109
00:11:25,790 --> 00:11:29,090
There's a night market across from the hotel.

110
00:11:29,540 --> 00:11:30,380
Have you been there?

111
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:31,840
Yes.

112
00:11:32,250 --> 00:11:34,800
There's a river and a temple over there.

113
00:11:35,420 --> 00:11:38,430
Oh, there's a temple too.

114
00:11:41,350 --> 00:11:42,600
There's a temple?

115
00:11:52,980 --> 00:11:54,070
Long time no see.

116
00:11:58,240 --> 00:11:59,030
Yeah.

117
00:12:00,700 --> 00:12:01,780
Long time no see.

118
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:23,140
Shall I drop you off at the bus terminal?

119
00:12:23,850 --> 00:12:25,810
Yes, exactly. Thank you.

120
00:12:27,520 --> 00:12:29,350
Is this your hometown?

121
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:32,730
Not my hometown, but I grew up here.

122
00:12:33,320 --> 00:12:35,400
Then it is your hometown.

123
00:12:36,860 --> 00:12:39,950
If you're student number 06, you two are in the same grade.

124
00:12:39,950 --> 00:12:41,780
Eun-ho, you two are friends!

125
00:12:41,780 --> 00:12:43,200
Dad, I repeated three years to get in.

126
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:44,660
Maybe we shouldn't talk.

127
00:12:44,660 --> 00:12:45,950
Jeong-won, are you hungry?

128
00:12:46,330 --> 00:12:47,540
I'm not hungry.

129
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:49,790
Eat before you go.

130
00:12:49,790 --> 00:12:51,210
I run a restaurant.

131
00:12:51,670 --> 00:12:54,130
Not to brag, but my restaurant is quite famous.

132
00:12:54,840 --> 00:12:56,550
Dad, just go to the terminal.

133
00:12:56,550 --> 00:12:58,510
What, can't I talk?

134
00:12:58,510 --> 00:12:59,260
No.

135
00:12:59,260 --> 00:13:02,850
You'd love it if you tried it.

136
00:13:05,350 --> 00:13:06,640
She's busy.

137
00:13:06,640 --> 00:13:07,680
I'm not busy.

138
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:08,730
What's your recommendation?

139
00:13:09,190 --> 00:13:10,980
Spicy seafood noodles with oysters.

140
00:13:12,270 --> 00:13:14,190
This is on the house.

141
00:13:16,030 --> 00:13:17,530
I pounded the octopus really well.

142
00:13:17,820 --> 00:13:19,320
Thank you, sir.

143
00:13:21,450 --> 00:13:23,950
What are you doing? Come eat with us.

144
00:13:29,710 --> 00:13:30,540
Is this to your taste?

145
00:13:30,960 --> 00:13:32,370
It's really delicious.

146
00:13:32,370 --> 00:13:33,920
Shall I pack some side dishes for you?

147
00:13:33,920 --> 00:13:35,040
No, thanks.

148
00:13:36,880 --> 00:13:38,090
You eat too.

149
00:13:42,300 --> 00:13:42,970
Eun-ho.

150
00:13:42,970 --> 00:13:44,430
When will you go see your mom?

151
00:13:44,430 --> 00:13:45,680
Tomorrow morning.

152
00:13:46,350 --> 00:13:47,470
Will it rain?

153
00:13:48,220 --> 00:13:50,560
The columbarium is indoors, it's okay.

154
00:13:50,560 --> 00:13:53,230
I mean your mom likes rain.

155
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:55,690
Your mom is so beautiful.

156
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:57,400
I look like my mom.

157
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:58,860
You look like me.

158
00:13:59,990 --> 00:14:01,070
Don't say that.

159
00:14:01,070 --> 00:14:02,030
What are you doing?

160
00:14:02,030 --> 00:14:02,740
I'm washing the dishes.

161
00:14:02,740 --> 00:14:03,660
Get out.

162
00:14:04,410 --> 00:14:07,580
Don't wash. Go out and wipe the table.

163
00:14:13,460 --> 00:14:15,080
Did you draw this?

164
00:14:15,250 --> 00:14:19,420
Some are drawn by me, and some by mom.

165
00:14:20,010 --> 00:14:21,170
Our painting styles are very similar.

166
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:23,430
You studied art?

167
00:14:23,430 --> 00:14:24,840
No, I studied computer science.

168
00:14:25,510 --> 00:14:26,140
What?

169
00:14:28,260 --> 00:14:30,020
Eun-ho, open this for me.

170
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:32,350
This is so easy.

171
00:14:34,900 --> 00:14:35,900
How come...

172
00:14:38,900 --> 00:14:39,730
Let me try.

173
00:14:46,870 --> 00:14:48,410
Let me pack some side dishes for you to take away.

174
00:14:48,410 --> 00:14:50,120
Really no need.

175
00:14:50,120 --> 00:14:51,500
Come again next time.

176
00:14:51,500 --> 00:14:52,750
Thank you for the treat, uncle.

177
00:14:53,040 --> 00:14:54,120
Stay safe.

178
00:14:55,250 --> 00:14:56,630
Take her home safely.

179
00:15:22,320 --> 00:15:25,030
Evergreen Orphanage

180
00:15:22,990 --> 00:15:24,650
-Thank you. Take care.
-Yeah

181
00:15:29,700 --> 00:15:31,370
Evergreen Orphanage
A warm home for the saplings

182
00:15:34,660 --> 00:15:35,750
Aren't you leaving?

183
00:15:35,750 --> 00:15:36,920
I'm leaving, bye.

184
00:16:04,860 --> 00:16:06,360
Who are you, please?

185
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:08,740
Is the president in?

186
00:16:09,110 --> 00:16:11,370
The president is resting today and went home.

187
00:16:12,490 --> 00:16:13,540
She went home?

188
00:16:13,540 --> 00:16:14,750
Yes.

189
00:16:14,750 --> 00:16:18,170
Her own home. This isn't her real home.

190
00:16:19,210 --> 00:16:22,670
Did you grow up here?

191
00:16:25,420 --> 00:16:27,510
Then come in and sit for a while before you leave.

192
00:16:27,510 --> 00:16:29,050
The other teachers are here too.

193
00:16:31,350 --> 00:16:32,510
No need.

194
00:16:33,220 --> 00:16:34,850
This is for the kids.

195
00:16:35,430 --> 00:16:37,270
You even brought gifts.

196
00:16:37,560 --> 00:16:39,770
Thank you so much.

197
00:16:39,770 --> 00:16:40,650
Goodbye.

198
00:17:20,270 --> 00:17:21,440
Are you finished?

199
00:17:22,230 --> 00:17:23,190
Yeah.

200
00:17:25,020 --> 00:17:27,280
What time does the sun set today?

201
00:17:35,280 --> 00:17:36,580
I'll drive, you sit in the back.

202
00:17:41,370 --> 00:17:43,080
-Can you ride?
-Yeah

203
00:17:48,090 --> 00:17:48,760
Hold me.

204
00:17:53,340 --> 00:17:54,140
Hold tight.

205
00:18:20,540 --> 00:18:23,330
What does it feel like to go home?

206
00:18:23,620 --> 00:18:24,670
Probably...

207
00:18:27,040 --> 00:18:28,750
The feeling of not wanting to eat spicy oyster seafood noodles anymore.

208
00:18:31,670 --> 00:18:34,050
I want to make a home, my own home.

209
00:18:34,470 --> 00:18:35,140
Home?

210
00:18:36,220 --> 00:18:37,640
Wow, home.

211
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:40,850
I want to make a game.

212
00:18:41,560 --> 00:18:43,140
You want to make a game?

213
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:44,140
Yeah.

214
00:18:44,730 --> 00:18:46,650
A game can have multiple endings.

215
00:18:47,820 --> 00:18:50,690
I want to make different and interesting endings.

216
00:18:50,940 --> 00:18:52,950
So you chose the computer major.

217
00:18:54,910 --> 00:18:57,490
Why didn't you go to the architecture department but to social welfare?

218
00:18:58,580 --> 00:19:00,620
Only social welfare has scholarships.

219
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:02,830
Did I have a choice?

220
00:19:06,580 --> 00:19:07,960
What are you doing?

221
00:19:08,590 --> 00:19:09,670
I'm making a wish.

222
00:19:09,840 --> 00:19:10,550
Making a wish?

223
00:19:10,920 --> 00:19:14,050
From the moment the sun touches the sea until it disappears.

224
00:19:14,050 --> 00:19:16,390
If you repeat your wish a hundred times, it will come true.

225
00:19:16,840 --> 00:19:17,890
You still believe that?

226
00:19:18,300 --> 00:19:19,390
It's true.

227
00:19:20,890 --> 00:19:24,230
It really works. Look, I got into college.

228
00:19:24,980 --> 00:19:26,900
Then am I your sacrifice?

229
00:19:27,690 --> 00:19:28,480
You just realized?

230
00:19:34,240 --> 00:19:34,990
It's now.

231
00:20:14,690 --> 00:20:16,450
JS Software Company

232
00:20:18,410 --> 00:20:19,740
The company is nice.

233
00:20:21,410 --> 00:20:26,620
You sitting here look like CG.

234
00:20:26,910 --> 00:20:28,460
It feels so unreal.

235
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:30,750
Yeah.

236
00:20:32,790 --> 00:20:34,170
This reminds me of the past.

237
00:20:36,340 --> 00:20:37,010
Yeah.

238
00:20:40,890 --> 00:20:42,180
Are you still looking?

239
00:20:43,640 --> 00:20:45,810
We definitely won't find it today.

240
00:20:45,810 --> 00:20:47,480
Han Jeong-won, Search

241
00:20:47,310 --> 00:20:48,770
I can't stand it.

242
00:20:48,770 --> 00:20:51,560
Come play games.

243
00:20:51,560 --> 00:20:52,650
Let's compete.

244
00:20:53,650 --> 00:20:54,360
One-on-one?

245
00:20:54,360 --> 00:20:55,110
One-on-one.

246
00:20:57,490 --> 00:20:59,240
Loser buys hamburgers.

247
00:20:59,240 --> 00:20:59,820
Okay.

248
00:21:00,410 --> 00:21:01,110
Okay.

249
00:21:02,120 --> 00:21:03,200
I will finally have a place to settle...

250
00:21:06,620 --> 00:21:09,500
Cyworld Minihompy

251
00:21:13,460 --> 00:21:15,840
Anbong Gas Station

252
00:21:16,630 --> 00:21:17,710
Anbong, Anbong, Anbong.

253
00:21:17,710 --> 00:21:19,010
Wait, start.

254
00:21:19,010 --> 00:21:20,180
Again, again.

255
00:21:20,180 --> 00:21:21,050
Wait.

256
00:21:21,050 --> 00:21:21,680
Cheering for you.

257
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:23,350
Cheering for what?

258
00:21:23,350 --> 00:21:25,010
-I'm cheering for you.
-What cheering?

259
00:21:25,010 --> 00:21:27,560
Look at me. Do I look better with or without glasses?

260
00:21:27,560 --> 00:21:28,180
Without.

261
00:21:29,180 --> 00:21:30,230
-Is that her?
-Don't exaggerate.

262
00:21:30,230 --> 00:21:31,270
This is a coincidence.

263
00:21:31,270 --> 00:21:32,980
Be natural, don't exaggerate.

264
00:21:32,980 --> 00:21:34,020
Don't worry.

265
00:21:35,020 --> 00:21:36,360
How much?

266
00:21:37,190 --> 00:21:38,190
Five thousand.

267
00:21:39,150 --> 00:21:40,240
Five thousand won?

268
00:21:41,740 --> 00:21:44,410
It's you, cult.

269
00:21:49,830 --> 00:21:50,870
Spicy seafood noodles.

270
00:21:50,870 --> 00:21:52,000
Yes, yes.

271
00:21:52,000 --> 00:21:52,870
You work here?

272
00:21:52,870 --> 00:21:54,290
Yeah. Why are you here?

273
00:21:54,290 --> 00:21:55,880
I came to refuel.

274
00:22:00,420 --> 00:22:02,380
Seoul is cruel to everyone.

275
00:22:03,590 --> 00:22:08,180
Ten times crueler to outsiders not born here.

276
00:22:09,350 --> 00:22:13,150
I've been wandering, wanting to settle down.

277
00:22:15,190 --> 00:22:18,820
But Seoul is cold and hard as concrete.

278
00:22:20,570 --> 00:22:22,900
Can't squeeze in, can't take root.

279
00:22:24,530 --> 00:22:28,740
But one day, I'll have my own home.

280
00:22:28,950 --> 00:22:33,040
Earn 10 billion won through games.

281
00:22:37,500 --> 00:22:38,590
Hey, cult.

282
00:22:40,090 --> 00:22:41,130
Hello.

283
00:22:42,010 --> 00:22:45,180
Game start, game start.

284
00:22:46,430 --> 00:22:47,220
Number five.

285
00:22:47,220 --> 00:22:47,800
One.

286
00:22:49,430 --> 00:22:50,310
Wait.

287
00:22:50,310 --> 00:22:51,640
Clockwise or counterclockwise?

288
00:22:51,640 --> 00:22:52,600
Turn like this.

289
00:23:05,610 --> 00:23:06,490
