No.

997
01:04:29,510 --> 01:04:29,890
Hand!

998
01:04:31,680 --> 01:04:32,720
You're touched, right?

999
01:04:33,060 --> 01:04:34,480
Your eyes are getting watery.

1000
01:04:34,480 --> 01:04:35,520
No.

1001
01:04:35,520 --> 01:04:36,140
Just a little bit.

1002
01:04:38,060 --> 01:04:39,270
On a leave of absence?

1003
01:04:40,190 --> 01:04:40,690
Accepted!

1004
01:04:40,820 --> 01:04:41,440
Okay. What?

1005
01:04:41,940 --> 01:04:43,360
Hi. Hello.

1006
01:04:43,360 --> 01:04:44,400
Here is your desk.

1007
01:04:45,570 --> 01:04:47,530
RUN!

1008
01:04:49,120 --> 01:04:50,700
Jackson's new work.

1009
01:04:51,120 --> 01:04:53,580
Pick something to copy, something safe,

1010
01:04:53,580 --> 01:04:55,000
and write a draft proposal.

1011
01:04:55,500 --> 01:04:56,790
Me? Copy?

1012
01:04:57,540 --> 01:04:59,210
Welcome!

1013
01:05:01,500 --> 01:05:02,130
Jeong-won, here.

1014
01:05:03,960 --> 01:05:04,590
How was today?

1015
01:05:05,010 --> 01:05:06,340
Something shocking happened.

1016
01:05:06,670 --> 01:05:07,170
What?

1017
01:05:07,800 --> 01:05:08,630
Han Jin...

1018
01:05:09,680 --> 01:05:13,720
Speed dial
001 Eun-ho
002 Jeong-won
003 Village Head

1019
01:05:09,930 --> 01:05:11,180
Number one is Eun-ho,

1020
01:05:11,600 --> 01:05:14,970
two is me, three is the Village Head.

1021
01:05:15,350 --> 01:05:17,600
You should be number one,
let Eun-ho be number two.

1022
01:05:17,980 --> 01:05:19,310
Right? I'm number one, aren't I?

1023
01:05:19,310 --> 01:05:20,100
Right.

1024
01:05:22,480 --> 01:05:23,690
I'm home.

1025
01:05:56,020 --> 01:05:56,720
Eun-ho.

1026
01:05:58,680 --> 01:05:59,310
Eun-ho.

1027
01:06:02,940 --> 01:06:03,860
I love you.

1028
01:06:26,340 --> 01:06:28,210
Jeong-won, it's Min-jae.

1029
01:06:28,460 --> 01:06:33,470
Jeong-won, it's Min-jae.
My company is looking for an intern
for architectural public education.
Let me know if you're interested.
No strings attached, just want to help.

1030
01:06:28,920 --> 01:06:32,180
My company is looking for an intern
for architectural public education.

1031
01:06:32,760 --> 01:06:33,840
Let me know if you're interested.

1032
01:06:42,190 --> 01:06:43,350
Have a good evening!

1033
01:07:13,680 --> 01:07:15,590
The sink is fixed.

1034
01:07:15,590 --> 01:07:17,680
It cost 90,000 won.

1035
01:07:18,390 --> 01:07:20,180
I'll send you my account info.

1036
01:07:21,140 --> 01:07:22,690
Of course, we'll renew the lease.

1037
01:07:23,600 --> 01:07:23,980
Yeah.

1038
01:07:26,110 --> 01:07:26,980
The deposit?

1039
01:07:27,820 --> 01:07:28,650
Lee Eun-ho.

1040
01:07:34,360 --> 01:07:36,870
I can't decide it myself.

1041
01:07:37,370 --> 01:07:39,330
I'll talk to my friend

1042
01:07:40,160 --> 01:07:41,200
and get back to you.

1043
01:07:46,540 --> 01:07:47,290
Damn it!

1044
01:07:50,090 --> 01:07:51,130
You must be hungry.

1045
01:07:51,460 --> 01:07:51,880
Yeah.

1046
01:07:51,880 --> 01:07:52,550
Let's eat.

1047
01:07:53,170 --> 01:07:54,130
Great!

1048
01:07:59,970 --> 01:08:00,970
Why are you so late today?

1049
01:08:01,600 --> 01:08:03,980
Had a really stubborn client,
so it ran late.

1050
01:08:05,640 --> 01:08:07,060
You weren't meeting someone else?

1051
01:08:07,650 --> 01:08:08,190
Who?

1052
01:08:10,190 --> 01:08:10,860
Nothing.

1053
01:08:12,070 --> 01:08:13,030
Give it to me, I'll handle it.

1054
01:08:13,360 --> 01:08:14,200
I've got it.

1055
01:08:14,400 --> 01:08:15,450
-Give it to me. -I've got it.

1056
01:08:15,700 --> 01:08:16,910
-Let me help. -I'll do it.

1057
01:08:17,110 --> 01:08:18,410
-You can't even open it.
-I said I'll do it.

1058
01:08:18,700 --> 01:08:19,660
-Give it to me.
-I'll...

1059
01:08:33,130 --> 01:08:34,720
What happened? Anything wrong?

1060
01:08:37,220 --> 01:08:38,180
The landlord

1061
01:08:39,970 --> 01:08:41,310
wants to raise the deposit.

1062
01:08:44,850 --> 01:08:46,890
So that's why you're stressed?

1063
01:08:47,730 --> 01:08:48,020
Yeah.

1064
01:08:48,980 --> 01:08:50,060
It's okay.

1065
01:08:50,900 --> 01:08:52,610
I can live anywhere with you.

1066
01:09:11,340 --> 01:09:14,960
Jeong-won, I used to think that
if I ever ran into you,

1067
01:09:16,130 --> 01:09:17,800
there was something I
really wanted to ask you.

1068
01:09:18,930 --> 01:09:20,090
Yeah? What?

1069
01:09:30,270 --> 01:09:30,900
A moment please.

1070
01:09:38,900 --> 01:09:41,530
Dad, why aren't you back yet?

1071
01:09:41,530 --> 01:09:42,320
Dae-un.

1072
01:09:42,620 --> 01:09:44,200
Why aren't you back?

1073
01:09:44,370 --> 01:09:47,120
Dad's plane can't take off.

1074
01:09:47,450 --> 01:09:48,500
I'll be back tomorrow morning.

1075
01:09:48,960 --> 01:09:50,460
Isn't it raining there?

1076
01:09:50,880 --> 01:09:52,210
Here? No, it's not raining here.

1077
01:09:52,380 --> 01:09:53,040
Really?

1078
01:09:53,670 --> 01:09:55,590
It's late now. You should go to sleep, Dae-un.

1079
01:09:56,090 --> 01:09:56,920
No.

1080
01:09:57,130 --> 01:09:58,800
Show me if the rain stopped.

1081
01:09:59,050 --> 01:10:00,260
Okay, I'll show you.

1082
01:10:00,380 --> 01:10:01,970
Show me the window.

1083
01:10:01,970 --> 01:10:03,970
What if the rain doesn't stop?

1084
01:10:03,970 --> 01:10:06,100
Wait, but it'll probably be dark.

1085
01:10:06,600 --> 01:10:07,810
Show me!

1086
01:10:09,100 --> 01:10:11,270
Show me! Show me!

1087
01:10:12,060 --> 01:10:14,480
Let's see. Let's go see.

1088
01:10:15,730 --> 01:10:16,940
Quick, quick.

1089
01:10:16,940 --> 01:10:17,650
We're here.

1090
01:10:22,280 --> 01:10:22,740
Look.

1091
01:10:24,370 --> 01:10:25,370
It's dark.

1092
01:10:25,740 --> 01:10:26,700
So dark, right?

1093
01:10:27,370 --> 01:10:29,000
Can't see anything.

1094
01:10:30,250 --> 01:10:31,370
I told you it was dark.

1095
01:10:33,040 --> 01:10:34,000
Dad will be back tomorrow.

1096
01:10:34,840 --> 01:10:35,920
Okay.

1097
01:10:36,630 --> 01:10:37,340
See you tomorrow.

1098
01:10:37,550 --> 01:10:39,050
Dad, I love you.

1099
01:10:39,260 --> 01:10:40,630
Yeah, Dad loves you too.

1100
01:10:40,840 --> 01:10:42,260
Dad, kiss.

1101
01:10:44,390 --> 01:10:46,310
Dad, you have to kiss me too.

1102
01:10:47,930 --> 01:10:48,770
Bye bye!

1103
01:10:48,890 --> 01:10:49,680
Good night!

1104
01:10:49,680 --> 01:10:50,430
Bye bye!

1105
01:12:21,400 --> 01:12:22,320
Ouch!

1106
01:12:30,490 --> 01:12:31,330
Wait.

1107
01:12:32,660 --> 01:12:33,910
Can you help me lift it up here?

1108
01:12:38,210 --> 01:12:39,000
It won't fit here.

1109
01:12:39,540 --> 01:12:40,880
-I think it will.
-No, it won't.

1110
01:12:41,590 --> 01:12:42,210
Just throw it away.

1111
01:12:43,090 --> 01:12:45,010
I think it will. Move.

1112
01:12:45,630 --> 01:12:46,220
Quick!

1113
01:12:55,270 --> 01:12:56,850
Ah, seriously!

1114
01:12:57,140 --> 01:12:59,310
Look at the size,
do you think this will fit?

1115
01:12:59,650 --> 01:13:00,610
Stop being stubborn!

1116
01:13:06,240 --> 01:13:07,110
I'll get the medicine.

1117
01:13:09,320 --> 01:13:11,240
No, I'll get it. I'm fine, really.

1118
01:13:20,630 --> 01:13:21,590
Are you coming back for
the Mid-Autumn Festival?

1119
01:13:22,040 --> 01:13:25,260
No, can't make it. I'm busy at work.

1120
01:13:26,840 --> 01:13:27,470
Gotta go.

1121
01:13:38,020 --> 01:13:38,730
Where is the conclusion?

1122
01:13:39,230 --> 01:13:40,440
You gave it to me yesterday.

1123
01:13:40,690 --> 01:13:43,320
Even if it's urgent, it still takes time.

1124
01:13:43,440 --> 01:13:46,240
You have time to submit garbage like this,

1125
01:13:46,610 --> 01:13:48,490
why didn't you do it properly beforehand?

1126
01:13:48,860 --> 01:13:51,870
Hey, I want to make cool stuff too.

1127
01:13:49,780 --> 01:13:51,910
Finding Jane
Game Development Proposal

1128
01:13:52,200 --> 01:13:54,200
It's not just you.

1129
01:13:54,200 --> 01:13:56,540
We don't do it because we can't.

1130
01:13:56,750 --> 01:13:58,370
Since you're here to make money,

1131
01:13:58,540 --> 01:13:59,830
stop talking and do what you're told.

1132
01:14:03,710 --> 01:14:05,130
What? You don't want to?

1133
01:14:06,590 --> 01:14:07,340
Get up!

1134
01:14:08,840 --> 01:14:10,680
Get up, you bastard!

1135
01:14:12,890 --> 01:14:14,600
-Sir! -Let me go! How dare you stare at me! You crazy bastard!

1136
01:14:14,600 --> 01:14:16,890
-Sir, don't! Please don't!
-You crazy bastard!

1137
01:14:17,060 --> 01:14:18,390
Hey! You gonna apologize or what?!

1138
01:14:18,680 --> 01:14:21,690
-Wait, let go of me! Apologize now! -Sir!

1139
01:14:22,860 --> 01:14:23,440
Sorry.

1140
01:14:25,650 --> 01:14:27,110
-Let go of me! -Sorry.

1141
01:14:34,700 --> 01:14:36,080
Why do you never answer your phone?

1142
01:14:37,580 --> 01:14:41,580
Never mind. Just text me. Yeah.

1143
01:14:43,420 --> 01:14:44,130
Who was that?

1144
01:14:45,210 --> 01:14:45,880
Gyeong-seok

1145
01:14:47,250 --> 01:14:47,750
Let me take it.

1146
01:15:01,600 --> 01:15:04,020
Aren't you busy?
Is it okay to skip work?

1147
01:15:04,520 --> 01:15:06,230
Took the day off.

1148
01:15:06,270 --> 01:15:08,690
That company can't function
without Eun-ho anyway.

1149
01:15:07,110 --> 01:15:12,450
Gyeong-seok
No, never mind.
Of course I don't. What money do I have?
Ask Seung-chan?
Should I ask for you?
No, it's okay.

1150
01:15:15,740 --> 01:15:19,160
Once you're settled,
aren't you gonna get married?

1151
01:15:21,660 --> 01:15:24,960
Getting married early is
so out of fashion these days, Uncle.

1152
01:15:25,420 --> 01:15:26,630
Just asking.

1153
01:15:27,380 --> 01:15:29,630
Anyway, you two start small,

1154
01:15:29,630 --> 01:15:31,590
build up slowly...

1155
01:15:32,170 --> 01:15:33,930
Don't act like you know.

1156
01:15:34,930 --> 01:15:36,800
Who says you can get married
without buying a house first?

1157
01:15:37,680 --> 01:15:39,640
Besides, Jeong-won might not
even want to get married.

1158
01:15:45,440 --> 01:15:48,520
Ah, I made that ox bone soup you like,
Jeong-won. Almost forgot.

1159
01:15:48,770 --> 01:15:49,610
Wait here for me.

1160
01:15:49,860 --> 01:15:51,780
Don't bother.

1161
01:15:59,740 --> 01:16:01,330
There's a limit to my patience.

1162
01:16:02,200 --> 01:16:03,160
Then stop holding it in.

1163
01:16:07,380 --> 01:16:08,130
Uncle!

1164
01:16:08,840 --> 01:16:10,500
-I slipped. -Ah, are you okay?

1165
01:16:15,590 --> 01:16:17,140
That's why you should close the shop.

1166
01:16:17,640 --> 01:16:20,060
How can you even run a shop like this?

1167
01:16:22,680 --> 01:16:25,600
Get out. Did I ask for your help?

1168
01:17:01,260 --> 01:17:02,100
Hey, Lee Eun-ho.

1169
01:17:04,140 --> 01:17:05,310
Stop going to that company.

1170
01:17:05,770 --> 01:17:07,270
Stop filing complaints
with the labor board.

1171
01:17:07,810 --> 01:17:09,190
What about living expenses
and medical bills?

1172
01:17:09,230 --> 01:17:12,190
Either quit and make games again,
or find another decent game company.

1173
01:17:12,190 --> 01:17:14,360
Anything but what you're doing now.

1174
01:17:15,570 --> 01:17:19,070
Jeong-won, I should be saying that to you.

1175
01:17:19,950 --> 01:17:21,030
Did you give up on being an architect?

1176
01:17:21,870 --> 01:17:23,740
If that showroom job suits you,

1177
01:17:24,080 --> 01:17:24,950
then keep doing it.

1178
01:17:25,790 --> 01:17:26,910
Who said it suits me?

1179
01:17:28,250 --> 01:17:30,330
Am I not doing all this for you?

1180
01:17:40,470 --> 01:17:42,930
Stop saying it's all for me.

1181
01:17:44,430 --> 01:17:45,890
Has Kang Min-jae contacted you?

1182
01:17:46,640 --> 01:17:48,600
About helping with the public project?

1183
01:17:49,560 --> 01:17:50,400
Do that.

1184
01:17:52,560 --> 01:17:53,860
I won't stop you. Do it!

1185
01:17:54,440 --> 01:17:57,110
He contacted me, but I never replied.

1186
01:17:57,360 --> 01:17:58,150
So do it.

1187
01:18:00,280 --> 01:18:02,740
Or you might blame me later. Go ahead!

1188
01:18:07,450 --> 01:18:08,290
What are you staring at? Go!

1189
01:18:12,380 --> 01:18:13,540
So you don't trust me now.

1190
01:18:38,900 --> 01:18:40,570
No, that's not it.

1191
01:18:44,410 --> 01:18:45,530
That's not it.

1192
01:18:46,410 --> 01:18:49,870
I'm sorry. There's nothing
I can do for you right now.

1193
01:18:50,210 --> 01:18:51,330
Let go of me.

1194
01:18:56,630 --> 01:18:59,720
That's not it, it's really not.

1195
01:18:59,920 --> 01:19:01,550
-Stop. -Look at me.

1196
01:19:01,550 --> 01:19:03,800
Look at me. I'm so sorry.

1197
01:19:03,840 --> 01:19:06,810
I shouldn't have said that. I'm crazy.

1198
01:19:06,810 --> 01:19:09,810
I'm a real jerk for saying that.

1199
01:19:11,600 --> 01:19:16,110
Eun-ho, ever since I met you,
I tear up at the smallest things.

1200
01:19:16,150 --> 01:19:19,230
I really hate it. I really do.

1201
01:19:19,280 --> 01:19:22,990
Jeong-won, listen to me.
Jeong-won, I'm sorry.

1202
01:19:25,240 --> 01:19:27,950
Jeong-won, I'm sorry, sorry.

1203
01:19:27,950 --> 01:19:31,250
What was wrong with me?
Jeong-won, I'm sorry.

1204
01:19:33,500 --> 01:19:35,080
I'm tired, Eun-ho.

1205
01:19:54,980 --> 01:19:56,440
RUN!

1206
01:19:56,900 --> 01:20:00,650
Grade 9 National Civil Service Exam
sees record-high competition rate,

1207
01:20:01,190 --> 01:20:05,910
with the Ministry of the Interior and Safety
reporting an average of 82.2 applicants per position.

1208
01:20:06,360 --> 01:20:12,000
Education administration posts topped the list
with an overwhelming 583.8:1 ratio.

1209
01:20:12,790 --> 01:20:15,000
New Employee Recruitment Interview

1210
01:20:13,660 --> 01:20:14,540
Mr. Jo Eun-ki?

1211
01:20:15,000 --> 01:20:18,210
-Yes, I made it to the final round.
-I see.

1212
01:20:20,380 --> 01:20:23,300
Eun-ho.

1213
01:20:20,460 --> 01:20:22,800
-I really wanted this. It's important.
-It is important.

1214
01:20:22,800 --> 01:20:24,090
You really know what I like, honey.

1215
01:20:24,090 --> 01:20:26,890
-Putting a drawer here would look great, right?
-Right.

1216
01:20:29,470 --> 01:20:30,930
Let's go check out the other room.

1217
01:20:43,780 --> 01:20:46,530
[Webmail] You have not passed the document screening phase for the first half of 2012 recruitment at Hanseong Game. Thank you for your interest.

1218
01:21:06,380 --> 01:21:07,220
What do you think?

1219
01:21:09,720 --> 01:21:11,350
Good,

1220
01:21:11,890 --> 01:21:13,600
but why is the plot so flat?

1221
01:21:14,180 --> 01:21:16,480
It takes some conflict to make it fun.

1222
01:21:17,270 --> 01:21:18,770
Yeah, I get that comment a lot.

1223
01:21:19,730 --> 01:21:25,150
But I don't want to write that kind of story.

1224
01:21:25,190 --> 01:21:27,950
But characters need to struggle
a bit to make it interesting.

1225
01:21:32,620 --> 01:21:33,910
-Hey, Eun-ho. -Yeah?

1226
01:21:35,250 --> 01:21:37,120
Even if others think it's boring,

1227
01:21:37,120 --> 01:21:38,500
let's just live a steady, peaceful life.

1228
01:21:50,220 --> 01:21:53,560
On Official Business

1229
01:21:53,600 --> 01:21:56,140
But what if Eric can't find Jane?

1230
01:21:56,560 --> 01:21:57,810
Isn't that a sad ending?

1231
01:22:02,810 --> 01:22:04,070
The world will turn black and white.

1232
01:22:44,610 --> 01:22:46,190
You always find me, no matter what.

1233
01:22:53,700 --> 01:22:57,240
You always escape to places
you know I'll find you.

1234
01:22:59,960 --> 01:23:02,080
Not escape. Leave.

1235
01:23:08,840 --> 01:23:09,920
Why did we break up?

1236
01:23:22,600 --> 01:23:25,610
-Just grab whatever.
-Hello, is this buy-one-get-one?

1237
01:23:27,230 --> 01:23:27,820
Ah, yes.

1238
01:23:30,610 --> 01:23:31,530
Hey, Eun-ho!

1239
01:23:34,610 --> 01:23:36,780
-Eun-ho! -Hey!

1240
01:23:49,340 --> 01:23:50,210
Yeah, Jeong-won.

1241
01:23:53,430 --> 01:23:56,010
What's with you?
Why are you in uniform?

1242
01:23:56,010 --> 01:23:57,050
Good to see you.

1243
01:23:57,050 --> 01:24:00,720
Cheers! Surprised how good
this foreign stuff is.

1244
01:24:00,970 --> 01:24:02,140
And there's more,

1245
01:24:02,480 --> 01:24:03,770
plenty there.

1246
01:24:04,270 --> 01:24:05,940
But this flat is really nice.

1247
01:24:06,560 --> 01:24:07,480
Did you buy it?

1248
01:24:07,480 --> 01:24:09,940
It's in my name, but it's my parents'.

1249
01:24:10,230 --> 01:24:11,190
It's mortgaged, mortgaged.

1250
01:24:11,610 --> 01:24:12,280
Look

1251
01:24:12,440 --> 01:24:13,860
what I found.

1252
01:24:15,070 --> 01:24:15,990
A magazine.

1253
01:24:16,200 --> 01:24:17,370
On the cover.

1254
01:24:18,700 --> 01:24:19,990
When did you get this?

1255
01:24:19,990 --> 01:24:20,990
Is that your dad?

1256
01:24:21,120 --> 01:24:22,750
You said you could cook,

1257
01:24:22,790 --> 01:24:23,830
but you can't even make ramen.

1258
01:24:24,330 --> 01:24:26,920
No, no. I'm just a figurehead.

1259
01:24:26,920 --> 01:24:29,590
It's all my dad's.

1260
01:24:29,590 --> 01:24:33,090
I just show up at the shop occasionally.

1261
01:24:33,510 --> 01:24:34,880
This life feels like a joke.

1262
01:24:34,880 --> 01:24:36,300
Still, I'm jealous.

1263
01:24:36,300 --> 01:24:37,970
You don't know how good you have it.

1264
01:24:37,970 --> 01:24:38,680
Tell me about it.

1265
01:24:39,550 --> 01:24:40,220
Eun-ho.

1266
01:24:40,260 --> 01:24:40,720
Yeah?

1267
01:24:41,470 --> 01:24:41,890
Come here.

1268
01:24:41,890 --> 01:24:42,350
Yeah.

1269
01:24:43,600 --> 01:24:45,350
It's been a while!
Come and talk to us.

1270
01:24:45,350 --> 01:24:46,810
First time seeing the Han River night view.

1271
01:24:47,400 --> 01:24:48,480
-Nice, right? -Yeah.

1272
01:24:49,270 --> 01:24:51,980
They say the Han River night view
gets depressing after a while.

1273
01:24:53,860 --> 01:24:55,780
Remember our club?

1274
01:24:56,070 --> 01:24:56,820
Blizzard.

1275
01:24:56,820 --> 01:24:57,530
Blizzard.

1276
01:24:57,530 --> 01:24:58,240
Blizzard!

1277
01:24:59,070 --> 01:25:00,120
-10 billion! 10 billion! -10 billion!

1278
01:25:00,120 --> 01:25:02,330
But really, it was impossible.

1279
01:25:02,330 --> 01:25:03,500
Of course it was impossible.
Where would we get 10 billion?

1280
01:25:03,500 --> 01:25:05,710
10 billion from gaming? That's absurd.

1281
01:25:05,710 --> 01:25:08,960
But back then, it was all ambition, all passion.

1282
01:25:09,250 --> 01:25:10,840
-Really.
-Exactly. It was possible because we were young.

1283
01:25:10,840 --> 01:25:12,920
-True.
-We didn't think about anything.
-Yeah.

1284
01:25:12,920 --> 01:25:13,800
Those were fun times.

1285
01:25:16,010 --> 01:25:18,130
Lee Eun-ho, let's go and have a drink.

1286
01:25:18,590 --> 01:25:19,590
-Another? -Yeah.

1287
01:25:20,430 --> 01:25:21,180
Let's go!

1288
01:25:29,770 --> 01:25:31,270
Is something bothering you?

1289
01:25:32,820 --> 01:25:33,230
No.

1290
01:25:35,570 --> 01:25:36,690
Looks like it.

1291
01:25:42,870 --> 01:25:43,870
Don't

1292
01:25:45,950 --> 01:25:47,460
wear that uniform when you're off duty.

1293
01:25:47,500 --> 01:25:48,750
People will look down on you.

1294
01:26:01,550 --> 01:26:03,010
Why aren't you developing games anymore?

1295
01:26:18,030 --> 01:26:18,780
Eun-ho,

1296
01:26:21,740 --> 01:26:23,780
you'll definitely succeed.

1297
01:26:24,830 --> 01:26:25,790
I...

1298
01:26:31,620 --> 01:26:33,500
Please, stop saying things like that, okay?

1299
01:26:39,670 --> 01:26:40,680
Did you do that on purpose?

1300
01:26:41,220 --> 01:26:43,140
What? You bastard!

1301
01:26:43,300 --> 01:26:43,970
What?

1302
01:26:44,350 --> 01:26:45,470
I was sitting there quietly,
what's your deal?

1303
01:26:47,470 --> 01:26:50,520
Who do you think you are?

1304
01:26:50,520 --> 01:26:51,640
Damn it!

1305
01:26:52,020 --> 01:26:53,610
Bastard, come here!

1306
01:26:53,610 --> 01:26:55,400
He hit me first!

1307
01:26:55,690 --> 01:26:56,480
Come here!

1308
01:26:57,150 --> 01:26:58,610
You bastard!

1309
01:26:59,360 --> 01:27:01,990
-Bastard!
-Kid's got a mouth on him!

1310
01:27:02,240 --> 01:27:03,530
Let go, let go!

1311
01:27:03,530 --> 01:27:04,490
What did I do wrong?

1312
01:27:04,530 --> 01:27:06,080
I was just sitting there!

1313
01:27:06,240 --> 01:27:07,330
Why are you doing this to me?

1314
01:27:08,240 --> 01:27:09,700
I was just sitting there!

1315
01:27:09,700 --> 01:27:11,040
Why?!

1316
01:27:14,380 --> 01:27:16,250
If you want to hit someone,
take it out on me.

1317
01:27:56,960 --> 01:27:58,210
Hello, Uncle.

1318
01:27:59,840 --> 01:28:01,880
Sorry I couldn't make it
for the memorial this time.

1319
01:28:01,970 --> 01:28:04,300
It's okay, don't worry about it.

1320
01:28:04,720 --> 01:28:06,840
I've called Eun-ho several times

1321
01:28:06,840 --> 01:28:08,220
but can't reach him.

1322
01:28:10,770 --> 01:28:12,640
He probably missed them.

1323
01:28:14,770 --> 01:28:16,600
You know how it is when you're job hunting.

1324
01:28:17,810 --> 01:28:20,150
He's studying right now, so he's not home.

1325
01:28:20,360 --> 01:28:21,280
I see.

1326
01:28:21,900 --> 01:28:24,490
Jeong-won, make sure you eat well.

1327
01:28:25,490 --> 01:28:27,370
I'll visit during the Mid-Autumn Festival.

1328
01:28:27,990 --> 01:28:28,830
Okay.

1329
01:28:29,160 --> 01:28:29,700
Yeah.

1330
01:28:45,970 --> 01:28:47,680
Eun-ho
Fighting
Kiss

1331
01:28:59,480 --> 01:29:01,020
It was supposed to rain.

1332
01:33:09,060 --> 01:33:09,730
Jeong-won.

1333
01:33:10,360 --> 01:33:11,020
Eun-ho.

1334
01:33:12,570 --> 01:33:15,110
I'd forgotten. I was doing fine. You too.

1335
01:33:16,240 --> 01:33:18,240
We've both changed a lot.

1336
01:33:21,240 --> 01:33:21,910
I know.

1337
01:33:31,590 --> 01:33:32,380
But

1338
01:33:33,960 --> 01:33:35,050
if

1339
01:33:36,840 --> 01:33:39,260
we hadn't moved into that semi-basement,

1340
01:33:41,180 --> 01:33:42,050
would we not have broken up?

1341
01:33:50,940 --> 01:33:51,650
No.

1342
01:33:53,980 --> 01:33:56,070
Even so, maybe we'd have lasted
another year or two.

1343
01:33:57,780 --> 01:33:59,070
What if

1344
01:34:00,450 --> 01:34:01,620
you'd waited for me?

1345
01:34:04,620 --> 01:34:05,910
Waited until the end?

1346
01:34:08,960 --> 01:34:11,630
Then you probably would never
have finished your game,

1347
01:34:11,630 --> 01:34:12,210
right?

1348
01:34:12,920 --> 01:34:13,460
So what if

1349
01:34:15,460 --> 01:34:17,210
we'd just gotten married

1350
01:34:18,420 --> 01:34:19,220
despite everything?

1351
01:34:21,050 --> 01:34:22,890
We would've gotten divorced for sure.

1352
01:34:22,930 --> 01:34:24,140
Stop it, Eun-ho.

1353
01:34:25,680 --> 01:34:26,970
No, one more.

1354
01:34:27,560 --> 01:34:28,600
Just one more question.

1355
01:34:33,060 --> 01:34:33,730
That day

1356
01:34:37,280 --> 01:34:38,610
if I'd gotten on the subway,

1357
01:34:41,160 --> 01:34:42,200
if I'd grabbed you.

1358
01:34:50,120 --> 01:34:51,500
If that's the case,

1359
01:35:01,380 --> 01:35:03,550
I would have stayed with you.

1360
01:35:05,510 --> 01:35:06,430
Forever.

1361
01:35:30,040 --> 01:35:32,370
No. We would have broken up eventually.

1362
01:35:36,090 --> 01:35:37,290
Because

1363
01:35:41,550 --> 01:35:44,140
you only packed kimbap
for yourself on that picnic.

1364
01:35:45,510 --> 01:35:46,510
So stingy.

1365
01:36:05,030 --> 01:36:05,700
I...

1366
01:36:07,910 --> 01:36:09,290
I lost you.

1367
01:36:15,170 --> 01:36:16,710
I let you go.

1368
01:36:19,920 --> 01:36:21,380
No. We,

1369
01:36:23,220 --> 01:36:24,930
we let each other go.

1370
01:36:30,350 --> 01:36:33,060
And it was the right choice.

1371
01:36:35,480 --> 01:36:37,190
I don't regret it, Eun-ho.

1372
01:37:26,150 --> 01:37:28,860
I always found romance movies frustrating.

1373
01:37:30,120 --> 01:37:33,620
Because the characters are fools
who only wake up after breaking up.

1374
01:37:30,780 --> 01:37:32,830
Eun-ho
Fighting
Kiss

1375
01:37:34,950 --> 01:37:36,750
And I was that fool.

1376
01:37:38,370 --> 01:37:41,420
Still, I believed that as long as
we were alive, things could be fixed.

1377
01:37:41,670 --> 01:37:44,880
So for no reason, I held on,
desperately wanting to fix things.

1378
01:37:51,850 --> 01:37:55,980
Jane is like a great sorceress
who manages all the colors in the world.

1379
01:37:55,980 --> 01:37:57,980
But the boss villain captures her.

1380
01:37:58,100 --> 01:37:59,100
What happens then?

1381
01:37:59,440 --> 01:38:00,690
The colors disappear.

1382
01:38:02,440 --> 01:38:03,980
Okay, last scene.

1383
01:38:03,980 --> 01:38:05,690
Look, there's the villain.

1384
01:38:05,690 --> 01:38:08,860
Jane's tied up behind him,
shouting "Help, help!"

1385
01:38:08,490 --> 01:38:10,910
Finding Jane. Game start.

1386
01:38:08,860 --> 01:38:09,860
What do we do now?

1387
01:38:09,860 --> 01:38:10,910
Go and save her!

1388
01:38:10,910 --> 01:38:11,780
You bet!

1389
01:38:12,030 --> 01:38:13,910
Jane, come quick!

1390
01:38:13,910 --> 01:38:14,910
You're getting caught!

1391
01:38:15,120 --> 01:38:16,250
Help!

1392
01:38:16,250 --> 01:38:18,750
I think they're chasing us! What do we do?

1393
01:38:19,460 --> 01:38:21,880
They're chasing, run!

1394
01:38:35,350 --> 01:38:38,060
I'm Lee Heung-bok, CEO of Lazarus. Regarding the co-development of Finding Jane

1395
01:38:40,270 --> 01:38:41,980
Transfer Entrance Exam: Past English Papers

1396
01:39:04,080 --> 01:39:07,710
Eun-ho

1397
01:39:24,360 --> 01:39:27,400
Eun-ho

1398
01:39:27,400 --> 01:39:31,820
Delete Contact

1399
01:39:31,820 --> 01:39:33,860
No records

1400
